+# Retrieval relevance cases
+
+M0 starts with routing measurement because the current harness already supports it.
+
+Use this folder for the next small retrieval baseline once the harness has a lightweight `retrieval` target.
+Do not add a new retrieval framework until this schema can run through the existing harness with a tiny diff.
+
+Suggested schema:
+
+```json
+[
+  {
+    "id": "retrieval-api-comparison-official-docs",
+    "query": "Compare Meta Marketing API and Google Ads API permissions and rate limits",
+    "surface": "research_evidence",
+    "relevant": [
+      {
+        "urlContains": "developers.facebook.com",
+        "grade": 3,
+        "reason": "Official Meta source"
+      },
+      {
+        "urlContains": "developers.google.com/google-ads/api",
+        "grade": 3,
+        "reason": "Official Google Ads source"
+      }
+    ],
+    "metrics": ["recall@5", "ndcg@10"]
+  }
+]
+```
+
+Rules:
+
+- Keep the set small and hand-verified.
+- Prefer official docs and source URLs as grade-3 relevance.
+- Use this to prove the M5 reranker improves retrieval before claiming answer quality improved.
